Description:
SOLD
This single fronted period charmer is sure to please growing families or savvy investors alike. It features high ceilings, picture rails, a period fireplace, polished floorboards, ducted heating & split system cooling. Three bedrooms provide ample accomodation, whilst a formal dining room leads to a central well-equipped kitchen overlooking a meals area. Those who like to entertain are sure to make avid use of the low maintenance rear yard, whilst off street parking for one car is provided via right of way access. Liveable now, it also provides excellent future potential for your own renovations/enhancements as time goes by. Currently leased until January 2019, it is returning $1868 per calendar month. This outstanding package is made complete by its 'blue ribbon' position, only moments to Sydney Rd. shopping/cafes, Coburg Train Station, West Coburg Primary School, Coburg North Village & The Melville Road Tram.

Description:
Leafy Locale, Active Lifestyle
Tucked in a leafy pocket seconds to De Chene Reserve and the Merri Creek Trail, this contemporary two bedroom residence offers a reverse living design, featuring an upstairs kitchen/meals/living, plus a ground floor living space. Ranging from a gas cooktop to a fan forced oven, dishwasher and rangehood, a full selection of stainless steel appliances meets with a stone countertop and tiled splashback in the kitchen. There are leafy aspects from each end of the flowing open kitchen/meals/living, which also benefits from reverse cycle heating/cooling and adjoins both a balcony and powder room. Downstairs you'll find a sitting room or study with sliding door access to a courtyard. Two double bedrooms offer heating, one has a built-in robe and both share a central bathroom with a shower and separate bath. A concealed laundry, storage, polished floorboards and automatic garage with interior access add practicality and appeal, and within a stroll you'll find trams, buses and Coburg High. Cosmopolitan Sydney Road is a short drive.

Description:
Updated Charm with Ample Space
Nestled behind gorgeous native gardens, you'll love this classic updated Edwardian, boasting dual living areas, high ceilings, spacious rooms and beautiful decorated ceilings and cornices, together with elegant new blackbutt timber floorboards.
Discover two large front bedrooms with period fireplaces, a spacious central dining room and lounge room (the dining room offering fantastic third bedroom potential - just add doors). Enjoy cooking for a crowd in the spacious kitchen with a freestanding Smeg 6-burner stainless cooker, overlooking an open-plan family zone and adjacent study.
Step outside to excellent covered decking, perfect for alfresco entertaining with an adjacent BBQ area, looking out over delightful landscaped gardens featuring rear lane access and a large garden studio/home office.
With great additional benefits including laundry and separate powder room for guests, split-system heating and cooling in the living areas, central heating throughout, and data cabling (ultra-fast NBN fibre-to-the-kerb coming later in the year), the location here is first-rate - just a 5-minute stroll to Coburg station and Sydney Road .
ROW rear lane access for off street parking if required.
Land size: 38.1 x 11.58= 441 m2 (approx)

Description:
Captivating Californian with Corner Credentials
Positioned to perfection in a premier Coburg neighbourhood, this gorgeous period home presents a ready-to-enjoy lifestyle opportunity along with plenty of scope to further enhance and expand in the future (STCA). Set on a sizeable corner block complete with rear ROW, the home's inviting interior comprises two genuinely large bedrooms (both with built-in robes) and contemporary-style central bathroom. Add to this an elegant formal lounge and separate dining room leading through to the updated kitchen with stainless steel cooking appliances and adjoining living/meals area. Other highlights of the home include ducted heating and split-system air conditioning (two units), original lead-light windows and solid timber floors. Step outside to an undercover deck with cafe blinds ideal for relaxing or entertaining, as well as an undercover BBQ area, lush backyard garden with high hedges for added privacy, workshop and tandem double garage (remote-control rollerdoor to Carlisle Street). Moments from Nicholson Street trams and local buses, it's also walking distance to schools, Merri Creek trails and parkland, as well as easy access to Coburg's vibrant shopping centre and Coburg Station. Description:
A Unique Slice of Coburg's History
Surrounded by lush gardens on an expansive 700sqm+ block, this landmark Victorian provides an incomparable lifestyle of period character, contemporary comfort and inner-urban convenience. The home itself (the northern half of the original residence) showcases two main bedrooms (extra-large master with BIRs) and stylish bathroom with marble-top vanity and freestanding bath. Add to this an elegant formal lounge and light-filled open living/dining area accompanied by a well-appointed kitchen with stainless steel cooking appliances, Asko dishwasher and adjoining butler's pantry. Heating and cooling, high ceilings, lead-light windows and polished floorboards, solar panels and Tesla Powerwall all add to the appeal, along with a delightfully deep backyard filled with established gardens, fruit trees and veggie patches, plus brick-paved entertaining spaces, versatile studio/third bedroom, garage and additional gated off-street parking space (both remote-controlled). Close to a range of lifestyle attractions including public transport options, popular parks, cafes and shops, Coburg West and St Fidelis primary schools, zoned for Strathmore secondary school, as well as quick and easy access to Citylink/Tullamarine Freeway. Absolutely one of a kind! In conjunction with Ian Reid's Vendor Advocacy Australia Pty Ltd.

Delight on Darlington

The residence is beautifully appointed including, stone bench tops, stainless steel appliances, impressive floor coverings including a combination of quality carpets and pristine tiling.

Delight on Darlington

Description:
'Byawatha'
Classic period charm meets dual living spaces and a sense of peace in a supremely convenient locale with 'Byawatha', a double fronted, three bedroom, two bathroom haven moments to Coburg Market, cafes, transport, schools and leisure facilities. Behind a central lounge is an open kitchen/meals/family where plentiful windows and a sliding glass door present leafy aspects. All kitchen essentials are in place with a full range of Chef appliances, including a dishwasher, teaming with a breakfast bar, pantry, deep drawers, cupboards and good counter space. A small deck runs across the rear of the home, and just below is a storage shed, garden and wide automatic carport with laneway access. Feature rich and with scope for enhancements and updates, the residence also offers a spa bathroom, ensuite, front bedrooms with a wide BIR/WIR, central heating and cooling plus a wealth of period touches including high ceilings with deep cornices, ceiling rosettes, leadlight, a corbelled archway and fireplace.

Description:
A Sophisticated Californian
Newly renovated, innovative design and exceptional quality have transformed this two bedroom Californian Bungalow into something truly special. Timber floors line a spacious open living domain, silver birch wall and ceiling panels contributing a sophisticated ambience. Smeg/Electrolux appliances, lustrous sleek cabinetry, waterfall Caesarstone breakfast bar and generous Butler's pantry define the ultramodern kitchen. The deluxe bathroom is similarly styled with equal effect, whilst even the laundry is attention worthy. Large bedrooms, one with open fireplace, include elegant built-in wardrobes. There's also off-street parking, shed/ studio, second toilet, high ceilings plus outdoor entertaining area.
A short stroll to Batman and Coburg train stations, Coburg North Village shopping precinct, Coburg North Primary School, Sydney Road shops and cafés, Farmer's Market, parks, and the Merri Creek bike trail strengthens appeal amongst home owners and investors.

Set in one of Coburg's most tightly held streets, it offers a second to none lifestyle opportunity and is only moments to Coburg Train Station, Sydney Road shopping/cafes, St. Fidelis Primary School & Coburg West Primary School. Seize the opportunity and see your vision come to life.

Description:
Family Elegance In The Pentridge Estate
Situated amid a family neighbourhood boasting homes of comparable style and quality, this spacious four bedroom residence is convenient to beautiful Coburg Lake Reserve, Coburg station, Merri Creek Trail plus Sydney Road shops, cafes and trams. Solid timber hardwood floorboards underfoot and plantation shutters throughout contribute warmth and sophistication to an interior boasting a large open living domain (modern fireplace) and theatre room. The kitchen presents lustrous stone counters plus quality appliances including integrated refrigerator and dishwasher while fully tiled ensuite and central bathrooms feature frameless showers, stone topped vanities and heating element which warms floor surface when required. Four large bedrooms assure ample accommodation and built-in outdoor café blinds enclose an all-weather alfresco deck. There's also zoned ducted heating/refrigerated cooling, remote double garage (internal access), separate laundry and alarm.

Description:
Quality and Style in a Perfect Position
Situated in a unique cul-de-sac with parkland across the road and instant access to Merri Creek trails, this captivating home provides a ready-to-enjoy lifestyle opportunity with its quality internal features and fabulous outdoor entertaining area. Beyond the picket-fenced garden and attractive facade, the home's inviting interior comprises two main bedrooms (one with BIRs) and modern central bathroom, light-filled lounge and adjoining dining room leading through to the family/meals area and updated timber-cabinet kitchen with dishwasher. Add to this ducted heating and split-system air conditioning, polished hardwood floors, laundry and second WC. Step outside to a fabulous undercover entertaining deck with cafe blinds and enclosed outdoor spa, as well as a versatile studio/office (or third bedroom), workshop/storeroom and established gardens, plus front carport and additional off-street parking space. Zoned to Coburg High School, it's also walking distance to Murray Road buses, Coburg Lake and swimming pool, as well as easy access to Nicholson Street trams and Coburg Hill Shopping Centre.
